<TITLE> Mohuiddin collects nomination papers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 13 (bdnews24.com)  Chittagong mayor ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury is seeking an unprecedented fourth time as mayor. He collected the nomination papers for the city corporation polls, scheduled June 17, twice on Thursday. His current tenure expires on June 25. Mohiuddin Chowdhury collected the nomination papers by himself by the second time on the same day at around 2.30pm amid much fanfare accompanied by a large contingent of party members and activists. Earlier in the day, Chittagong metropolitan Awami League's general secretary Quazi Inamul Haque Danu also collected the nomination paper on behalf of the mayor from the city's district election office on Thursday. He said the party in its Wednesday's meeting decided to nominate Chowdhury as the candidate. According to the schedule announced by the Election Commission, the last date for filing nominations is May 20 and Jun 1 for withdrawals. On Wednesday four people, including AL MP Akhteruzzaman Chowdhury and former president of Chittagong Chamber of Commerce and Industry, Saifuzzaman Chowdhury Javed, collected nomination papers. The elections to the port city council were last held on May 9, 2005. EC deputy secretary Jasmine Tuly has been appointed as the returning officer for the CCC polls. In the last elections, mayor Mohiuddin Chowdhury beat BNP's Mir Mohammad Nasir Uddin. The CCC will be the only one of the six city corporations holding elections before expiry of its current tenure. According to the Local Government (City Corporation) Law2009, elections have to be held within 180 days after the current tenure expires.
